2022-08-19

Coverage Simulation

Ran

  • 100 simulations with
  • 25 subjects, each going through
  • 10, 25, 50, 75, and 100 trials with
  • 1000 bootstraps each

Coverage is proportion of simulations in which the true curve was between the 5th and 95th quantiles of the bootstrapped distribution

Parameters

Average pointwise coverage by trial

Average pointwise coverage by time

Quantile needed for 90% band coverage

We dont have this for bdots as bdots does not naturally produce quantiles. Instead, here we set \(\alpha = 0.1\) and considered pointwise coverage to be whether or not the generating curve fell within the \(\mu_t \pm t_{\alpha^*}\hat{\sigma}_t\) band. Since the bootstraps do appear to generally be normally distributed at each point, this range is actually more generous than simply having determined the collection of bootstrapped curves, measuring the quantiles from there.
